oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tibial Neurectomy for the Correction of Spastic Paresis in Calves
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Weaver, A. David
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: spastic paresis
gastrocnemius
superficial flexor
tenotomy
tenectomy
hock joint
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The conventional treatment of spastic paresis by gastrocnemius and partial superficial flexor tenotomy or tenectomy is often disappointing due to recurrence of the clinical signs of an overextended hock joint some weeks later as a result of a fibrous union.
